# WHAT IT IS
#   mastodon-bluesky-sync is a bi-directional cross-poster
#   between Mastodon (or any Fediverse instance supporting the
#   Mastodon REST API — Pleroma, Akkoma, Iceshrimp, etc.) and
#   Bluesky / the AT Protocol.  Run it on a cron and it:
#     • polls your Mastodon account's authored posts via the
#       megalodon-rs typed `client.get_account_statuses(...)`
#       walk, builds a typed Bluesky `app.bsky.feed.post`
#       record (with embedded media, alt text, and rich-text
#       facets via the `bsky-sdk` rich-text helper), and posts
#       it through `bsky_sdk::BskyAgent::create_record(...)`;
#     • polls your Bluesky account's authored posts via
#       `bsky_sdk::BskyAgent::api::app::bsky::feed::
#       get_author_feed(...)`, builds a typed Mastodon
#       `Status` create payload, and posts it through
#       megalodon's `client.post_status(...)`;
#     • optionally syncs *deletions* (an unfav / unboost on
#       one side gets mirrored on the other) and *favorites*
#       (a like crosses over too).
#
#   Designed for the steady-state "I want one timeline mirrored
#   across both networks" use case — not for one-shot post
#   broadcasts.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/args.rs clap-derive
#                       `Args` struct; extracted via `gh api
#                       repos/klausi/mastodon-bluesky-sync/
#                       contents/src/args.rs`)
#
#   mastodon-bluesky-sync [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -c, --config <PATH>            Config file
#                                    [default:
#                                    mastodon-bluesky-sync.toml]
#     -n, --dry-run                  Dry run — print what would
#                                    be synced but don't write
#                                    any new posts, deletions,
#                                    or favorites
#         --skip-existing-posts      Skip all existing posts
#                                    (use this if you only want
#                                    to sync future posts;
#                                    sets the "starting
#                                    timestamp" to "now" so the
#                                    syncer ignores history)
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `megalodon >= 0.14` declared in
#   Cargo.toml — `megalodon` is THE canonical Rust Mastodon /
#   Fediverse SDK, maintained by h3poteto (h3poteto/megalodon-
#   rs, 100+ stars; the predominant typed Rust client for the
#   Mastodon REST API and its drop-in extensions in Pleroma,
#   Akkoma, Friendica, GNU social, Iceshrimp, Misskey-style
#   forks, and Firefish — paired with the same author's
#   `megalodon` npm package for JS/TS, the only typed SDK that
#   maintains *bidirectional* protocol parity between Rust and
#   TypeScript on the same major version).  megalodon-rs
#   exposes the typed `megalodon::generator(sns, base_url,
#   access_token, user_agent) -> Box<dyn Megalodon + Send +
#   Sync>` factory that dispatches between
#   `entities::SNS::{Mastodon, Pleroma, Friendica, Firefish}`
#   backends, the typed `Megalodon` trait with
#   `client.get_account_statuses(account_id, options)` /
#   `client.get_account(account_id)` /
#   `client.verify_account_credentials()` /
#   `client.post_status(text, options)` /
#   `client.get_status(id)` /
#   `client.delete_status(id)` /
#   `client.favourite_status(id)` /
#   `client.unfavourite_status(id)` /
#   `client.reblog_status(id)` /
#   `client.unreblog_status(id)` /
#   `client.bookmark_status(id)` /
#   `client.unbookmark_status(id)` /
#   `client.get_home_timeline(options)` /
#   `client.get_public_timeline(options)` /
#   `client.get_local_timeline(options)` /
#   `client.get_tag_timeline(tag, options)` /
#   `client.get_list_timeline(list_id, options)` /
#   `client.get_status_context(id)` /
#   `client.upload_media(file_path, options)` /
#   `client.get_media(id)` /
#   `client.search(query, type, options)` /
#   `client.get_account_followers(account_id, options)` /
#   `client.get_account_following(account_id, options)` /
#   `client.follow_account(account_id, reblogs, notify)` /
#   `client.unfollow_account(account_id)` /
#   `client.block_account(account_id)` /
#   `client.mute_account(account_id, notifications)` /
#   `client.get_notifications(options)` /
#   `client.dismiss_notification(id)` /
#   `client.get_instance()` /
#   `client.streaming_url()` /
#   `client.user_streaming()` /
#   `client.public_streaming()` /
#   `client.local_streaming()` /
#   `client.hashtag_streaming(tag)` /
#   `client.list_streaming(list_id)` /
#   `client.direct_streaming()` request + response model, the
#   typed `entities::Status` /  `entities::Account` /
#   `entities::Attachment` (with `kind: Image | Video | Gifv |
#   Audio | Unknown`) / `entities::Mention` /
#   `entities::Tag` / `entities::Card` / `entities::Poll` /
#   `entities::Application` / `entities::Notification` /
#   `entities::Instance` / `entities::Filter` /
#   `entities::List` / `entities::Marker` /
#   `entities::Source` / `entities::Relationship` /
#   `entities::FeaturedTag` / `entities::Activity` /
#   `entities::Conversation` / `entities::Field` schemas, the
#   typed streaming `Streaming` trait + `Message` enum
#   (`Message::Update(Status)`, `Message::Notification(...)`,
#   `Message::Delete(String)`, `Message::Conversation(...)`,
#   `Message::Heartbeat`), and the OAuth helpers
#   (`client.register_app(client_name, options)`,
#   `client.fetch_access_token(client_id, client_secret,
#   code, redirect_uri)`).  mastodon-bluesky-sync's
#   `src/lib.rs` constructs a `megalodon::generator(SNS::
#   Mastodon, instance_url, Some(access_token), None)` client
#   per sync cycle, walks the authored-statuses pagination
#   cursor, and routes each `entities::Status` through the
#   typed Bluesky AT-Proto builder before reposting it.
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/klausi/mastodon-bluesky-sync/contents/
#         Cargo.toml
#       → megalodon = ">=0.14"
#       → clap = { version = ">=3.2.22", features = ["derive"] }
